      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;CLASS: Necromancer&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;HP: Huge factor when we consider Lifeburn, and how many AE's in raids we can take. How much of a beating a mob can do before we are smooshed.&lt;BR&gt;Mana: Another Huge State, Problem with INT Casters is trying to balance the HP/Mana Ratio of our class's. We all Need Mana to do DPS, we are not a Melee that can keep on going without mana. So if we go OOM then we are done for the fight till we can regen.&lt;BR&gt;Endurance: Ya, we don't use this at all.&lt;BR&gt;AC: Very Important for all Class. All around is low due to being cloth but we still need it for when we draw agro accedently.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;HP Regen: Yes this is important for all, the more regen can help when you have that nasty 500hp dot, if you have 80 regen you only take 420(hrrmm) hp dmg.&lt;BR&gt;Mana Regen: Same, when dealing with mobs mana drain effects this is important for all casters and hybrids.&lt;BR&gt;Endurance Regen: no effect&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Strength: Situational at most, with some zones that lower your stats this has a huge factor in movement, otherwise normal play has nothing really to do with our class.&lt;BR&gt;Stamina: Singly the most important stat in the game due to this sets your base HP's.&lt;BR&gt;Agility: Very important stat for avoiding damage.&lt;BR&gt;Dexterity: Nothing important.&lt;BR&gt;Charisma: Nothing that I know of.&lt;BR&gt;Intelligence: Mana(Deex3)&lt;BR&gt;Wisdom: Nothing important&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cold Resist: Important to all for resisting spells and raising your chromatic resists average.&lt;BR&gt;Disease Resist: See cold resists&lt;BR&gt;Poison Resist: See cold resists&lt;BR&gt;Magic Resist: See cold resists&lt;BR&gt;Fire Resist: See cold resists&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Attack: Nothing&lt;BR&gt;Delay: Nothing&lt;BR&gt;Damage: Umm not sure what your asking about but, damage has everything to do with our charicters, more damage we produce the faster the mob dies (Deex3)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Range: Read Damage&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Haste: Ya, when I am swinging my Deathwisper cause I am bored ya haste is fun.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Combat Effects: Nothing Iportant.&lt;BR&gt;Shielding: For all Class's this is important.&lt;BR&gt;Stun Resist: Read Shielding&lt;BR&gt;Strikethrough: Nothing to do with our class.&lt;BR&gt;Spell Shield: Very Important&lt;BR&gt;Avoidance: Very Important&lt;BR&gt;Accuracy: Whats This?&lt;BR&gt;DOT Shielding: Very Important&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Skill Mods: These are so light of a difference we never see anything.&lt;BR&gt;Click Effects: Clickes are what make and break most high end raiders. Extra HP, ManaRegen, Resists, Damage when you are OMM. They are very usefull.&lt;BR&gt;Proc Effects: Not for us sorry&lt;BR&gt;Worn Effects: Very Important to us, Faerune is by far one of the best effects for the toon with low AA's.&lt;BR&gt;Focus Effects: This is by far the bigest factor for any casters dps or healing power.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
