      <title>Re: The Importance of Stats</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=13471#M13471</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;CLASS: &#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Monk, of the millionth season&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;HP: No brainer - With warriors in short supply, I find myself tanking a lot these days&lt;BR&gt;Mana: none&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Endurance: with 10k endurance when grp buffed, and only using phantom and claws, Ive found my end is just not enough even after little usage.&lt;BR&gt;AC: I'm not sure how important it is, as it is debatable, IMHO ac for monks doesnt really matter at all.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;HP Regen: Not really all that important with new regen&lt;BR&gt;Mana Regen: not.&lt;BR&gt;Endurance Regen: Really important&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Strength: I always enjoy having strength maxed. More strength = more dps. Nuff said.&lt;BR&gt;Stamina: Fairly important.&lt;BR&gt;Agility: I like to have this maxed at all times&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Dexterity: Combine with 4 damage augs and double attack, again, this should be maxed&lt;BR&gt;Charisma: not important&lt;BR&gt;Intelligence: not important&lt;BR&gt;Wisdom: not important&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cold Resist: &lt;BR&gt;Disease Resist: &lt;BR&gt;Poison Resist:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Very important, in that prismatic, special kinda way. Need these to be in the 800+ range with new raid mobs&lt;BR&gt;Magic Resist: &lt;BR&gt;Fire Resist: &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Attack: The more the better&lt;BR&gt;Delay: as long as ratio is under .6 does it really matter? Not really running drag races&lt;BR&gt;Damage: always important&lt;BR&gt;Range: We need more monk usable items Like the stoneroot starfish, shuriken of eternity, etc. Carrying around piles of throwables like I used to was a no-go and dusty soriz pouch... well, lets not go there.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Haste: Would love more haste, but IMHO over 50% is just getting crazy&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Combat Effects: Very important for monks who tank (agro keeping) and those of us with a lot of damage augs.&lt;BR&gt;Shielding: psh.&lt;BR&gt;Stun Resist: Always a good thing&lt;BR&gt;Strikethrough: Unless tanking, not important&lt;BR&gt;Spell Shield: Fairly important, especially to raiding monks&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Avoidance: God for monks&lt;BR&gt;Accuracy: This, is my favorite attribute. The more accuracy, the more you land hits. Therefore, more DPS overall. Currently I only have +25 to accuracy, which translates to like... 2% or something? More items could have +acc on them.&lt;BR&gt;DOT Shielding: Not too important, DOT shielding never seems to do anything&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Skill Mods: Not at all important unless under level 30&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Click Effects: More clickies!! Who cares what it does, clickies are teh best!.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Proc Effects: For tanking monks, good stuff&lt;BR&gt;Worn Effects:&amp;nbsp;Depending on effect... fero, cleave, etc... good&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Focus Effects: w/ev. =)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As a personal rant... New items tend to be a little ...off, perhaps?&amp;nbsp; Of course, a good general rule as to how good an item was, was how many HP that item had. Now, with the last 3 expansions or so, I have seen more and more items with a ton of HP but garbage stats.&amp;nbsp; Is the trend going to be toons with over 10k hp unbuffed, but are useless otherwise? I think some items need to be retuned, so that instead of everyone looking for items that have the highest hp, that they have to wear armor in combinations so as to even out the resists and stats.&amp;nbsp; For a person on loot council, I tend to see items that have accuracy, avoidance, and other melee features, that are dru/mnk/bst... and I FEEL that most of the time the loot goes to the druids because of the *effect* which could be better healing or whatever, and has uber HP. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;BY THE WAY.... PLEASE*****&amp;nbsp; &amp;lt;---can you guys make more armors that make me look like a monk, not a druid? all im askin for is a strappy chestpiece, not the world in my hand. ;)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Shanxi&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
