&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Methinks you misunderstand the root of the word Ranger.&amp;nbsp; You're mistaken in your assumption that it means ranged combat, for it does not.&amp;nbsp; The word Range refers to the area over which the Ranger roams/wanders/patrolls, or the act of that roaming/wandering/patrolling.&amp;nbsp; A Ranger is one who roams over an area, patrolling that area, wandering it.&amp;nbsp; Ranger as a title has absolutely nothing to do with how one fights, cooks, or where&amp;nbsp;one lives.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Also, rangers can bow kite prior to 59+45.&amp;nbsp; Get a ton of arrows, make sure you keep the mob snared, maybe even rooted,and plink away.&amp;nbsp; Kiting was the recommended method for soloing the Ivy Etched Armor quests, as I recall - well before Luclin gave us AA's.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Archery damage does need a boost, yes.&amp;nbsp; At least, that is what I get from reading ranger boards; ranged damage is supposed to be 85% of melee damage from what I understand, yet it falls far short of that (depending on gear and AA's).&amp;nbsp; For me, personally, I've got no real problems with my archery damage.&amp;nbsp; I get more out of my bow than I do out of my hammer and Darkglint when I use Trueshot, and more out of my melee weapons when I'm not using Trueshot.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Just remember : Ranger does not mean Archer.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
