    <item>
      <title>Re: The Importance of Stats</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=13490#M13490</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&amp;nbsp;Just as a different perspective to the above bard, who looks like he spends a lot of time soloing and perhaps less time raiding.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;CLASS:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Bard, L75&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;Progression:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt; In a high-end raiding guild (defeated A. Ro in PoR), but I still wear a few Time items.&amp;nbsp; I've been in and out of playing for a few years so I missed big chunks of raiding during DoN, DoD and PoR and am seriously undergeared because of it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;How I spend my time online:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt; Raiding primarily, and I'm generally a grouping bard otherwise.&amp;nbsp; I started to hate soloing when PoP came out and never recaptured my desire to do it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;General Statement about Bards and Gear&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;In general, I feel bards are the least gear-dependent class in the game.&amp;nbsp; I can sing my songs without mana (for the most part), so I can bring benefit to others even completely naked.&amp;nbsp; Bards aren't primarily someone who gets beat by the mob during normal xp groups (except as a puller).&amp;nbsp; Soloing allows me to chant kite from a distance.&amp;nbsp; (Soloing using charm or soloing summoning mobs or casters requires more ability to withstand blows, but we're not warriors.)&amp;nbsp; Back when I was pulling LDoN hards with 2800 mana and 5k buffed HP, it took a lot of skill to be a bard.&amp;nbsp; Now that I'm 10k unbuffed with 9k mana (which is woefully undergeared for a bard in my guild, but that's the price I pay for real-life work getting in the way and being a PT raider), I have the buffer that allows me to be lazy when it comes to typical group stuff.&amp;nbsp; I forgot to loot my corpse in Direwind (death by LD zone crash, yay!) the other day and pulled probably 3 bunches of mobs naked before my group pointed it out.&amp;nbsp; Granted, my group tank and monk jumped on mobs forthwith when they arrived or I would've been one-rounded if I took damage from more than one mob.&amp;nbsp; But my point is to illustrate that I could actually be a bard doing my pulling/group DPS thing completely naked.&amp;nbsp; (However, having all of the mitigation/avoidance AAs and maxxed resists from singing PoV matters A LOT.)&amp;nbsp; You can't be a tank and do your tanking thing completely naked, or be a cleric and do your healing thing completely naked, or be a caster and do your DPS thing completely naked for 10 or 15 mobs and not notice it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;HP:&lt;/font&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt; Highly important when making gear choices, but I will defer to tanks and clerics for a long time on the highest HP items.&amp;nbsp; I wouldn't necessarily take a 400 HP item over a 300HP item if the 300HP item had better worn effects, resists, or AC.&amp;nbsp; Even being 4000-5000HP below the rest of the bards in the guild, they still want me in a 54-person raid because my survivability (thanks, Fade) is still good enough to want me because of what my songs bring to the raid.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Mana: With the new level 75 songs, a greater consideration than ever.&amp;nbsp; Highly important in gear choices, but probably equal or slightly less than HP.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Endurance:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; I don't pay attention to it at all, but if our gear stopped having it completely, I might end up unable to use a disc.&amp;nbsp; But since our discs have such long recast times (a problem in itself), endurance hardly matters.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;AC: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;This might actually beat out HP when making gear choices, but I'm a defensive bard.&amp;nbsp; I need to be able to withstand hits when pulling or when I find myself inadvertent raid rampage tank, or when soloing goes wrong (in the rare times that I do it).&amp;nbsp; With current raid content, my ability to mitigate seems to do more than raw extra HP, unless it's a huge AC difference.&amp;nbsp; I like the 1 AC = 4HP rule of thumb, meaning I'd take a piece of gear with 20 extra AC and only 10 extra HP until the other option was an 80-100HP gain.&amp;nbsp; Being 500AC behind the rest of the guild bards means I'm not a raid puller, period.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;HP Regen:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Very important.&amp;nbsp; I'm the one who begs the shaman or druid for regen on the raid, and keeps SA just for the extra regen.&amp;nbsp; Because bards are often the last healed in a raid group (especially if you're MT bard), my ability to heal myself through regen is crucial.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Mana Regen:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; With the cap at 15, I don't pay attention to it much so long as I stay at the cap.&amp;nbsp; However, being at the worn cap is VERY important as a bard since we don't get the benefit of clarity, our manasong, etc.&amp;nbsp; Even with OOC regen now, because of the new uses for mana with TSS songs, mana regen during fights is still very important.&amp;nbsp; From a designing gear perspective, that means you still need to include mana regen on items or we'll be stuck keeping old gear to remain at the cap.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Endurance Regen:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Don't even pay attention to it.&amp;nbsp; I use endurance for a disc here and there but have never been OOE when I needed it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Strength:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; This has become harder and harder to come by on gear.&amp;nbsp; It used to be plentiful so it wasn't a factor, but I'm under the STR cap now because it was left off of OOW/DON/DOD bard gear.&amp;nbsp; As a tradeskilling bard, this is important to me.&amp;nbsp; I also do see a difference with my hit dmg when I don't have shaman buffs to max it.&lt;br&gt;Stamina: Highly important until you hit the cap for HP reasons.&amp;nbsp; Plentiful enough that it's not a factor when making gear choices, but it would become an issue if gear stopped including STA.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;Agility:&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/b&gt;Highly important because of the implications for defense.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Dexterity:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; At 75 and raiding, this seems moot.&amp;nbsp; Does it even matter for missed notes once you get the AAs?&amp;nbsp; Our instrument caps were so low that it stopped mattering.&amp;nbsp; If it's playing a part in my ability to hit, I guess I don't see it.&amp;nbsp; Not important when making gear decisions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Charisma:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Important for bards because of the implication for lull resists.&amp;nbsp; Making lullable raid trash will make charisma that much more important.&amp;nbsp; (I want to bonk all bards who say it makes mez and charm land better or last longer, because in my experience, it doesn't).&amp;nbsp; Also important for DA, but the last time I got DA in a raid was... well, so long ago I can't remember.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Intelligence:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;As a tradeskilling bard, this is highly important to me.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Wisdom:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Sometime a while back, I was told wisdom mattered with song resists or some nonsense like that.&amp;nbsp; I don't think it does anything for us, so you can feel free to leave it off bard gear.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;Resists:&lt;/font&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt; They're all pretty much of equal importance so I'll discuss them as a whole.&amp;nbsp; My base resists matter up to (resist cap - 357).&amp;nbsp; Yes, coincidentally, that's how much I can buff my resists with PoV.&amp;nbsp; So I look at resists to be sure I can keep myself unbuffed at 350-400 and don't worry about it after that.&amp;nbsp; Raid AEs were so difficult to resist for so long that resists became of even less meaning, so I'll be interested to see what the changes to the resist code and the new Corruption resist types do to raiding.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Attack:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Highly important.&amp;nbsp; I'm often hitting raid mobs or higher-end group mobs, so my attack vs. their AC is really important to my DPS.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Delay:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&amp;nbsp; More important to me than damage.&amp;nbsp; Because we can be at max overhaste all the time, bards like fast weapons.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Damage:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; High damage, low delay weapons are things of beauty for bards.&amp;nbsp; I'd take a faster weapon over a slow, high damage weapon though because of our haste abilities.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Range:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Song range is a big deal.&amp;nbsp; Raid bards need to be able to hang with casters and reach a mob.&amp;nbsp; They also need to be able to single-handedly wipe an entire raid by pulsing on a monk before he feigns on the pull.&amp;nbsp; Range on throwing items (now that we can throw!) is a HUGE consideration so we can add more damage in ranged raid fights.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Haste: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;As the masters and mistresses of haste, no self-respecting bard can be below the haste cap.&amp;nbsp; I will make sure I have a 45% worn haste item even if I have to keep a crappy Time helm.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Combat Effects:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Worth making an effort to max.&amp;nbsp; My DPS needs all the help it can get.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Shielding:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Less important than avoidance because shielding does less when the mob's DB is already lower. &amp;nbsp; Avoidance always helps.&amp;nbsp; Important, but less important than Spell Shield, DoT Shielding, and CE.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Stun Resist:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Very important for pulling and raiding.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Strikethrough:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Not very important, which is why I find it humorous that so much bard gear has it.&amp;nbsp; We're not tanks, so there's no reason we can't get ourselves behind the mob to hit it.&amp;nbsp; In the occasion when we are tanks, we don't rely on our melee DPS to keep aggro anyway.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Spell Shield:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; HUGE.&amp;nbsp; Taking less damage from raid AEs when you're the last one who's going to be healed in your group is a big deal.&lt;br&gt;Avoidance:&amp;nbsp; Possibly worth more than raw AC to me, which means it's worth a lot.&amp;nbsp; It will be interesting to see how TSS raid mobs affect the bard AC softcap.&amp;nbsp; Avoidance is more important to me than shielding because it matters all of the time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Accuracy:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; I need all of the DPS help I can get.&amp;nbsp; If only Accuracy did more.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;DOT Shielding:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Ditto spell shield, although perhaps a teensy bit less important than Spell Shield because group mobs primarily cast spells and not DoTs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Skill Mods:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; I can't think of a single Skill mod that affects bards.&amp;nbsp; I've heard this is because our instrument mods are considered skill mobs, but I've also heard our instrument mods are considered our Focus Effects and that makes more sense.&amp;nbsp; Our instrument skills don't play the role they should in our missed notes/fizzles, so adding those as a skill mod wouldn't be useful.&amp;nbsp; I keep +pick lock mod gaunts in my bag, but our lockpick skill is still so far below where it should be that it doesn't matter much.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Click Effects:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&amp;nbsp; VERY important in gear selection.&amp;nbsp; I love click effects, especially clicks that give me some special ability.&amp;nbsp; I keep bags full of gear with click DS, regen, HP, invis, resonance, shrink, etc.&amp;nbsp; Most song click gear is "meh" because the designers choose the wrong songs.&amp;nbsp; I'd bid max on any piece of gear with click Selos.&amp;nbsp; &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;PLEASE let bards retire the Composer's Greaves.&lt;/font&gt;&amp;nbsp; Here's how you determine which songs to include as clicks:&amp;nbsp; Don't include songs that are part of our normal twists because it's too cumbersome to click gear every 12 seconds.&amp;nbsp; (If you could stopsong macro a click effect, it would be an entirely different story.)&amp;nbsp; But pulling songs like HoS, Selos, DI, and slow are AWESOME on gear because you can save a song slot.&amp;nbsp; I'd love right-click Highsun (and mobs that aren't immune).&amp;nbsp; Even click PoV would be used for pulling.&amp;nbsp; Oh, and stop giving illusion clicks to everyone!&amp;nbsp; Bards love illusions, and we love them being a special thing to fight over with rogues.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Proc Effects:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; BIG deal, because so much of bard DPS depends on proc damage.&amp;nbsp; Procs are of lessening important as we gain double attack skill, but it's still something that's really important when choosing weapons.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Worn Effects:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Cleave, Fero, Improved Dodge, Improved Parry... all of that stuff is really, really important because it significantly improves bard DPS and mitigation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff33"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Focus Effects:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Putting Instrument Mods in this category, then I'd say GIGANTICALLY a big deal.&amp;nbsp; I want to be able to bag my epic 2.5 and have worn mods that will cap me.&amp;nbsp; I'd love to have 3.0 worn mobs for each instrument.&amp;nbsp; I have to have high worn mods so it makes a big difference in gear choices until I get one of each type.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I know I'm months behind in posting, but hopefully you'll still find this food for thought.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Calli&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
