&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;HP: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Probably the single most important stat to have.&amp;nbsp; Running out of HP is worse than anything else.&amp;nbsp; I will chose gear in part for HP values over Mana.&amp;nbsp; Some necros prefer mana augs to hp augs, that makes no sense at all to me.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Mana: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Comes with gear, and augs that also have HP, as such it is never a consideration for gear choices.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Endurance:&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt; Never a consideration.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;AC: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Never a consideration.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;HP Regen:&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt; important (easy to max), very important for young and non-raiding necros in order to counter hp loss due to &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;lich&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Mana Regen: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;important (easy to max)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Endurance Regen:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Strength: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Only important for carrying things around, matters more at lower levels lower geared.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Stamina: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;sta = hp, so important to max, easy to do so&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Agility: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Dexterity: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Charisma: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Intelligence: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;int &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;= mana, so important to max, easy to do so&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Wisdom: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Cold Resist: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Comes with gear, not something to focus on&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Disease Resist: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Comes with gear, not something to focus on&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Poison Resist: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Comes with gear, not something to focus on&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Magic Resist: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Comes with gear, not something to focus on&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Fire Resist: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Comes with gear, not something to focus on&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Attack: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Delay: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Damage: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Range:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Haste:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Combat Effects: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant. (fun for playing with primaries that fall far short of being epic replacements)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Shielding: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Not entirely un&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;imortant. Good to have, hard to max, and we don't get much bonus from it.&amp;nbsp; Anything that we'd want to kill we probably don't want to be getting hit by in the first place, and we certainly won't get hit enough by it that shielding will make much of a difference.&amp;nbsp; That said, I'd still like to see more shielding on necro usable gear.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Stun Resist: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Important.&amp;nbsp; Getting stunned sucks, can determine if you live to get a FD off or not, and not getting the FD off may mean a long corpse run for a raid, or even summoning and reclearing tons of annoying trash.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Strikethrough: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Spell Shield: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Very important.&amp;nbsp; Max this asap.&amp;nbsp; With good HP and max spell shielding you can live through 20k DT's, until they fix those!&amp;nbsp; But it's really great for AE DD encounters when you get smacked every 30 or so seconds by a big one.&amp;nbsp; Less hp loss means less lifetapping or less healing from the group healers.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Avoidance:&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt; Important, and very easy to max with gear/augs.&amp;nbsp; Avoiding being hit means you can make that fd check and recover a raid, or tap tank stuff with a greater chance of survival, granted it has to be relatively gimpy mobs compared to what a SK or Shammy can solo tank.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Accuracy: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Unimortant.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;DOT Shielding: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Very important.&amp;nbsp; Max this asap.&amp;nbsp; This is useful for mostly the same reasons that Spell Shielding is.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Skill Mods: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Not very important.&amp;nbsp; If they come on gear and are &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;font color="#ff3300"&gt;EITHER &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Alteration (lifetaps and many DoTs) &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;font color="#ff3300"&gt;OR&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Conjuration (other DoTs) then that's great and all, but I would never ever go out of my way to get one.&amp;nbsp; Dodge wouldn't be too bad either, but the use would be minimal and not worth obtaining any gear specifically for it.&amp;nbsp; Any other skill mod (aside from tradeskill mods and thus not really a class issue) are kind of useless.&amp;nbsp; For instance Evoc on &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=83620" target="_blank"&gt;Blighted Teardrop Necklace&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;boggles the mind.&amp;nbsp; Yeah we do get evoc spells, but I rarely nuke undead,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=10546&amp;amp;source=Live" target="_blank"&gt;&#xD;
            Wilting Foliage&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt; is a bad joke which should be replaced with something useful, and it's debatable that &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=10482&amp;amp;source=Live" target="_blank"&gt;&#xD;
            Demand for Blood&lt;/a&gt; actually increases DPS over the DoT it replaces in the lineup.&amp;nbsp; Effectively, we don't get any benefit from Evoc mods.&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Click Effects: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Absolutely important.&amp;nbsp; The best items a necro can posess have click effects.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=64067" target="_blank"&gt;Deathwhisper&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;, &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=14730" target="_blank"&gt;Circlet of Shadow&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;,&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=70928" target="_blank"&gt; Blightbringer's Tunic of the Grave&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=24890" target="_blank"&gt;Holgresh Elder Beads&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;, &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=15867" target="_blank"&gt;Wand of Impenetrable Force&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=68217" target="_blank"&gt;Ossein of Limitless Time&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;, other &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;clicky dots, insta-clickies etc etc...&amp;nbsp; collecting these alone is a game within the game.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Proc Effects: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Useless mostly for necros, though there are some cute toys with procs.&amp;nbsp; Most of the items I've seen added are just that.&amp;nbsp; Unless you're screwing around I don't see much use for&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=83632" target="_blank"&gt;Lilac, Cruel Manipulator&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;or&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=46906" target="_blank"&gt;Bale and Brimstone&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp; &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;There are previous toys like&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=22946" target="_blank"&gt;Kelp Hilted Mace&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=89892" target="_blank"&gt;Enspelled Wand&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=21876" target="_blank"&gt;Wand of Temporal Power&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;that you really have no reason to use either.&amp;nbsp; At least the mace has a proc mod that doesn't suck.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=5774" target="_blank"&gt;Boneshear&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=26526" target="_blank"&gt;Scythe of Sundering&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;may be two of the most useful proc items a necro can get.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Worn Effects: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Absolutely important.&amp;nbsp; Epic worn effect for example.&amp;nbsp; The &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=46906" target="_blank"&gt;Bale and Brimstone&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt; is a joke if it's meant to be an epic replacement.&amp;nbsp; No necro in his or her right mind would give up 4, 8 or 10% crit mods.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;Focus Effects: &lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Absolutely important.&amp;nbsp; You need Fire Magic and Poison damage foci, as well as det spell haste, det mana pres, det range, det duration, and bene duration is very very nice for lich and dmf.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Biggest gear problems:&lt;br&gt;Juggling foci so you're not out one.&amp;nbsp; I know necros who get an upgrade as far as HP goes and bag the upgrade until they can replace the focus on the slot the first upgrade would go in.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For lower levels and low hp regen, lich damage is an issue that the class has had by design.&amp;nbsp; Many just learn to deal with it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;HP &amp;gt; All.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;Some of the nicer items have good hp numbers but end up with melee &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;mod2's &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;on them instead of caster &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;mod2's&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;, while the caster &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;mod2 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;items have lower hp.&amp;nbsp; I'd sacrifice mod2's now and then for more hp on the all/all items, when the dkp price becomes reasonable.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by ---Xislaben--- on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;11-14-2006&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;05:36 PM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
