    <item>
      <title>Re: The Importance of Stats</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=13395#M13395</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;From a casual point of view, as a Bard. 1 being the lowest, 10 being highest.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Merloc-DEV wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hello Everyone,&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Before I get too far along, I thought I'd ask for some feedback from players on how they view different stats with respect to the class(es) they play.&amp;nbsp; Obviously, I have my own view on things, but I'd like to know how any why people have their own views.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What I'd like, is for you to&amp;nbsp;take a look at this list of the basic item stats (feel free to include any others that I left out), and let me know how and why they think they are, or aren't, important to your class.&amp;nbsp; All comments are useful, and feel free to use current items as examples to illustrate your points if you feel the need.&amp;nbsp; Be sure to INCLUDE THE CLASS name, so I can put your feedback in context.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hopefully, I'll gain some new insights that will help me do my job better.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Thanks.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-------&lt;BR&gt;CLASS:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;HP: 10 (pullers need to be able to survive a round or two)&lt;BR&gt;Mana: 7 (mana is good, always comes with the hp anyways)&lt;BR&gt;Endurance: 0 (bards don't use it)&lt;BR&gt;AC: 9 (high ac is used to mitigate the initial damage, but not as important as hp)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;HP Regen: 3 (I never look for it in gear, but there's still some importance to it)&lt;BR&gt;Mana Regen: 7 (mana regen is easily capped these days)&lt;BR&gt;Endurance Regen: 0&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Strength: 7 (important for certain skills, and higher attack)&lt;BR&gt;Stamina: 10 (more hp = more survival)&lt;BR&gt;Agility: 8 (good for the defense, but not as good as sta)&lt;BR&gt;Dexterity: 8 (one of the factors in missed notes, combat skills, and others)&lt;BR&gt;Charisma: 9 (the other factor in missed notes, hardest to raise for a bard with the current gear out there)&lt;BR&gt;Intelligence: 7 (more mana is good, but i can function well even if i had a 2 or 3k mana pool.)&lt;BR&gt;Wisdom: 0&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cold Resist: 4 (everyone knows bards can raise the resists the highest, and with mobs having resist mods of -400 or -500 on AE's, resists become more obsolete.&lt;BR&gt;Disease Resist: 4&lt;BR&gt;Poison Resist: 4&lt;BR&gt;Magic Resist: 4&lt;BR&gt;Fire Resist: 4&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Attack: 7 (bards are not masters of DPS by any means, but a little extra is always nice.)&lt;BR&gt;Delay: 6 (low delays mean more hit aggro, bards don't need extra aggro.)&lt;BR&gt;Damage: 10 (high damage means more damage output)&lt;BR&gt;Range: 1 (bards generally don't use throwers for initial aggro like monks do)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Haste: 6 (with the possibility of 90% self buffed haste, it's not necessary to overload bard gear with haste.)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Combat Effects: 6 (more procs are fun, but not necessary to the bard class)&lt;BR&gt;Shielding: 9 (ranks up there with AC, more survivability on those initial hits is key, nobody wants to keep rezzing the puller)&lt;BR&gt;Stun Resist: 8 (stuns from behind are a killer for pullers, more chances to avoid this are good)&lt;BR&gt;Strikethrough: 2 (bards generally attack from the back or sides, much like rogues do)&lt;BR&gt;Spell Shield: 9 (mitigation of raid ae's and spells is good)&lt;BR&gt;Avoidance: 10 (avoiding attacks is very nice for a bard)&lt;BR&gt;Accuracy: 6 (more dps is nice, but not necessary)&lt;BR&gt;DOT Shielding: 9 (mitigation of raid ae's = more survivability)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Skill Mods: 7 (only gets a higher rank because of mods like +parry or +dodge)&lt;BR&gt;Click Effects: 8 (bards love their clickies!&lt;BR&gt;Proc Effects: 6 (bards get a decent chunk of their dps from procs)&lt;BR&gt;Worn Effects: 8 (most worn effects are beneficial to bards in some way, whether it be increasing dps or avoiding damage)&lt;BR&gt;Focus Effects: 0 (useless on bard gear)&lt;BR&gt;-------&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;</description>
