      <description>CLASS:Monk&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;HP:Important &lt;br&gt;Mana:N/A &lt;br&gt;Endurance:Important &lt;br&gt;AC: Past 1250 doesn't matter. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;HP Regen:Important for soloing and grouping non downtime. &lt;br&gt;Mana Regen:N/A &lt;br&gt;Endurance Regen:Important &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;Strength:Easy to hit caps. &lt;br&gt;Stamina: Ditto. &lt;br&gt;Agility:Same. &lt;br&gt;Dexterity:Slight difficulty in getting to max caps. &lt;br&gt;Charisma:Important for buying/selling, tradeskills. &lt;br&gt;Intelligence:Important for tradeskills would like more. &lt;br&gt;Wisdom:Important for tradeskills but easy to max caps. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;Cold Resist: Decent with gear in game. &lt;br&gt;Disease Resist: Decent. &lt;br&gt;Poison Resist: Decent. &lt;br&gt;Magic Resist:Need alot more, Epic 2.0 has none of it. &lt;br&gt;Fire Resist:Class resist, easy to get high. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;Attack:Hard pressed to crack 2100 non buffed. &lt;br&gt;Delay:Would like to see more under 19 delay weapons. &lt;br&gt;Damage:Very important. &lt;br&gt;Range:Need more summoning throwers. &lt;br&gt;Haste:Extremely important. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;Combat Effects:Helps dps so needed. &lt;br&gt;Shielding:Helps on pulling alot. &lt;br&gt;Stun Resist:Lovely to have while pulling run 7/8 mobs. &lt;br&gt;Strikethrough:Not often tanking but it helps. &lt;br&gt;Spell Shield:Like it alot. &lt;br&gt;Avoidance:Easy to max. &lt;br&gt;Accuracy:Like to see more balance of it on items. &lt;br&gt;DOT Shielding:Wonderful for tacvi and raid encounters. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;Skill Mods:Like em for tradeskills,avoidance,dps. &lt;br&gt;Click Effects:Very important for debuffings mobs. &lt;br&gt;Proc Effects:Would like to see higher lifetap augs. &lt;br&gt;Worn Effects:Sheer lack of usible Class 4's and above. &lt;br&gt;Focus Effects:Iffy subject. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Now a longer explanation on some.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Magic Resist: I've noted a utter lack of higher end magic resist on monk usible gear, this needs to be looked at for some balance issues. Sure you can get 350 in it, but try getting it to past 400 without buffs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Range: Most of the older monk community has been reliant on their summoned throwers for tagging mobs to bring to groups/raids/solo. We don't use ranged slot items other than throwers unless we are doing dps and someone else is doingthe pulling. While there are a few in game, the rarity of them is something that is an issue. From 50 range to 250 range throwers, there are alot of player made ones but the downside is it becomes costly to make 400 which might last you 5 days at most.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Intelligence:Not so useful for a monk in combat but outside for tradeskills its the lowest stat you can find when working on tradeskills.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Skill Mods:There are so many different skill mods in game its hard to keep current effects after an upgrade due to them usually being locked on a one slot usible item. I love the mutli slot items such as Assistant Researcher's Symbol due to it not being phased out by a higher level belt or a higher level neck item when I do upgrade one or the other.Eventually it will be phased out, but it has longevity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Worn Effects:There are alot of modifiers such as Cleave and Ferocity and the like but the difficulty in achieving gear with mods such as Block III and Dodge III and above is sorely lacking on monk usible gear.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Proc Effects:Current lifetap procs cap at 250 crit, having two of them allows for a potential of 500 off both but with mobs hitting for 900 to 2900 in groups would like to see a higher end aug with at least being able to match 3/4's of the potential dps the mobs hand out.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If ya got any questions/issues as to my other listings don't hesitate to annotate or ask.&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Sinthala_LoL on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;10-05-2006&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;03:38 PM